2. License Scope Classification

   This project contains intellectual property of different natures, each
   governed by distinct licensing terms:

   2.1 Protocol Specification Documents (docs/draft-*)

       The textual content of the IETF Internet-Draft
       "draft-sakistudio-sass-00" and subsequent versions included in this
       project is subject to dual licensing:

       (a) IETF Trust License:
           Pursuant to BCP 78 (RFC 5378) and the IETF Trust's Legal
           Provisions Relating to IETF Documents
           (https://trustee.ietf.org/license-info), the textual content
           of these specification documents is protected under the IETF
           Trust license. Any contributions to these documents are
           considered rights granted to the IETF Trust under BCP 78.

       (b) Saki Studio Copyright:
           The original design concepts, architectural ideas, and
           security mechanism designs described therein (including but
           not limited to the 6-Response State Machine, Safety Gradient,
           Transparent Branching, Vi Swap, Tarpit, and related
           innovations) remain the intellectual property of Saki Studio.

       Users may reference and implement the protocol described in these
       specification documents in accordance with the IETF Trust's
       licensing terms. However, commercial derivative use of the
       original design concepts requires written permission from
       Saki Studio.

   2.2 Implementation Source Code (saki-ssh-daemon/, saki-ssh-client/,
       go-sakissh/, SakiAgentSSH-Daemon/, SakiAgentSSH-Client/, SakiSSH/,
       saki-ssh-wasm-payload/, sakissh-ca/, proto/)

       All implementation source code (including Rust, Go, Swift, and
       Protocol Buffers definition files) is copyrighted by Saki Studio.

       Saki Studio grants users a non-exclusive, non-transferable,
       revocable limited license to use this source code for personal
       learning, research, or non-commercial development purposes.

   2.3 Binary Distributions (release/, bin/)

       All pre-compiled binaries, installation packages (DMG, MSI),
       and package manager manifests (Homebrew Cask, Scoop, Winget)
       are copyrighted by Saki Studio. Unauthorized redistribution
       is prohibited.


